	publisher = {Cold Spring Harbor Laboratory},
	abstract = {Summary Small eukaryotic genome assemblies based on long reads are often close to complete, but still require validation and editing. Tapestry produces an interactive report which can be used to validate, sort and filter the contigs in a raw genome assembly, taking into account GC content, telomeres, read depths, contig alignments and read alignments. The report can be shared with collaborators and included as supplemental material in publications.Availability Source code is freely available at https://github.com/johnomics/tapestry. Package is freely available in Bioconda (https://anaconda.org/bioconda/tapestry).Contact john.davey{at}york.ac.ukCompeting Interest StatementThe authors have declared no competing interest.},
